The table always deserves a pretty outfit too!
⠀
Looking back with love to Elizabeth and Andrew’s wedding day created with gorgeous florals by @tulipinadesign and captured by @ktmerry 🤍

From weddings to showers to babies and parties!
⠀
It’s always such a treat when our couples come back to us to celebrate the important stages of their lives together! The celebration of a new member of the family is our favorite especially when they’re this cute! We’re so grateful that we were able to create this beautiful day for Elizabeth & Andrew and the most adorable birthday boy - Arlo 🤍 
His smash cake started with some gentle petting (so appropriate for his animal-loving heart) and once he discovered the yummy peach flavor inside he dove right in! How we love watching our couples grow their families! Can’t wait to share more party fun!
⠀
⠀

Yours truly…
⠀
How we love a good mail day! Giving your guests a thoughtful experience for your wedding day we believe starts at the mailbox! 📬
⠀
Lauren and Sam’s beautifully designed paper by Prim and Pixie was no exception! It was intentionally curated with French influence to give a nod to their love of Provence, baguettes and rosé! We love setting expectations with a pretty and playful hint of what’s to come!
⠀
Photo by @dearloversphoto

Sometimes the excitement of anticipation is the best part of knowing a surprise is coming! I love how the curious question of what’s inside brings out the kid in all of us! From eagerly hurrying to open the next door on the advent calendar to running to the tree on Christmas morning, it all holds a bit of magic, sometimes even more than the present itself it seems!
⠀
For Cara and Christian’s wedding, we wanted to add a bit of this joy and excitement and planned a special interactive guest experience to get guests to their seats! With the help of @heytherecupcake_ we created handmade chocolate molds hiding a little secret inside for each of the guests …their table numbers!
⠀
We always encourage our clients to break the mold and we loved the chance to take things literally this time! Hoping this season brings you all the most beautiful of surprises!
⠀
⠀
⠀
Photo by @spostophoto

We’ve been counting down the days to share our oversized advent calendar seating display and Christmas came early this year! So thrilled to be on @stylemepretty today reminiscing Caroline & Matt’s beautiful wedding day where the past kissed the present underneath mistletoe in a ceremony by the sea @rosewoodmiramarbeach 
⠀
When you get married the weekend before Christmas, you can't help but want to bring in all the joy of the holiday season and your favorite family traditions as you gather with those you love most. For our sweet Caroline + Matt, who wanted a warm, inviting and intimate day, we gave a nod to the season with snow globes we custom-created and personalized to hold guest names and table numbers. Guests were further favored with ornaments that they pulled from opening drawers below with numbers corresponding to the guest's table assignments while honoring the family’s tradition of collecting a new ornament every year.
⠀
Lush florals from @native_poppy in shades of cranberry, rosy red, shell pink, and evergreen with touches of icy blue kept it merry and bright! So many lovely December details that made our hearts sing! Be sure to pop over to @stylemepretty to see the full feature with a special guest appearance 🎅🏻
⠀
⠀
⠀

God Morgan! Lucia day with my little loves! In an attempt to surprise the kids this year we pushed our Saint Lucia day tradition to this week and held it following a Christmas cousin sleepover. It was a chance to all be together and the children doubled and tripled up in our bedrooms after a fun night of family gathering, playing Christmas bingo and caroling to the neighbors. My darling niece Ruby joined my Milla for the first time in waking early and preparing the hot cocoa and cookies for the other sleeping little ones. Such a treasure to wake alongside my sister and help them get dressed while trying to contain their morning giggles as Milla taught and practiced the song with Ru and their candlelight glowed in the stairwell. 🕯️ I will never tire of seeing Milla tiptoe up to the bedrooms singing and looking like an Angel and this year to have the two of them was such a treat! #saintluciaday #cookiesandcocoa #christmastradition

Fa La La La Love to everyone!
⠀
Just one more sleep! We’ve been setting up a special surprise activity for the kids tomorrow morning to find their presents and are equally as excited to share it with them as to get back to our regularly scheduled sleeping schedule! It’s going to be another long one tonight but all for the love of that Christmas magic! ✨ Wishing you all the merriest!!
⠀

Imagine the feeling of driving along the coast of Mexico with your windows down, breathing in the beauty of the ocean to one side as you take in the desert scape of the Baja region on the other. Sunlight pours onto your skin and you're reminded of long summer nights as you find yourself surrounded by all the things and people you love on intimate gathering tables as the sun sets over clusters of agave plants, dried grasses, and cacti.
⠀
All of this and much more was our inspiration for a beautifully curated day for Lauren & Sameer that we are honored to see on SMP today! Such an incredibly talented team to work with! Be sure to pop over to @stylemepretty to see the full feature with all the details!

Another year of cherished memories! This year was crazy busy and blessed at the same time! We shared our love with a record number of couples and continued to develop and grow our team in great ways! Within our family, our little ones have grown into big kids with big hearts that bring us so much joy as they’ve been pursuing all their own creative outlets from guitar, singing, saxophone, art and dance! What a wonderful year it’s been!
⠀
We’re so grateful for all the moments and the love we have felt from each of you! Happy New Year from our family to yours! We’ve got some amazing weddings ahead and couples that we can’t wait to work with in 2023! So excited for all that is to come!
⠀
An extra large Love and thanks to @lucymunozphotography for capturing our family so beautifully! Always such a gift experiencing our photographers talent up close and personal.

For a girl who loves all things warm California sun and flowers, what could be better than a wedding in a greenhouse? Traci and Jason choose to marry at Dos Pueblos in the stunning Santa Barbara area overlooking the ocean with their closest family and friends by their side.  Excited to be over on @stylemepretty today sharing all the details!
⠀
The floral backdrop was a nod to their favorite song by Van Morrison "You give me love, love, love, crazy love." Hand-calligraphed cards with fresh chocolate cosmos held guests' names and table assignments. The space was filled with eye-catching floral installations by @sirenfloralco with hanging beaded chandeliers illuminating the space that made for the moodiest of romantic vibes!

From old love to new love
⠀
There’s nothing quite like the bond between grandmother and granddaughter and getting to witness such strong and beautiful relationships, especially on one’s wedding day as was captured with Lauren and her darling grandma is always one of the highlights of our job!
⠀
Cherishing more of these moments and memories! Here’s to a new year and to new families! We’re holding onto the love that we have for those that have come before and are excited for those we have yet to meet this year! Seeing new families form and create relationships that will be there for generations to come is something that will forever be an honor to be a part of!
⠀

⠀
We’re in love with these colors of deep emerald, soft mint green and soft butter yellow with pops of citrus warm accents! Their love story all began on a velvet green couch, where they spent hours talking and later it was that same couch that Chaz proposed on! Velvet chairs and couches appropriately filled the space on their wedding day as well along with subtle festival vibes where table numbers were various musicians they’ve loved seeing together, artfully done in watercolor by @fourthingspaper

Dreamy night overlooking the ocean ✨
⠀
When Margaret came to us with her sweetheart Chris in hand, we quickly learned they had that something rare and once-in-a-lifetime kinda love. Their story was inspiring and reminded me that things don’t always happen according to the timing that we may have hoped or planned for and yet with continued faith those moments often find us in unexpected ways. The happy beginnings can start at any time in our stories.
⠀
While she met Chris later in her life. Margaret had found the one who was worth the wait! Thrilled to share in their joy and with just 3 short months to plan we were so excited to get these two married! Fall tones and ocean views at @olehansonbeachclub enhanced the occasion!
⠀
Loving these peach, coral, lush colors with soft butter yellow touches paired with sand and walnut neutrals! Sometimes things just fall beautifully and naturally into place the way they were always meant to 🤍

So excited to be over on @100layercakelet today celebrating cutie patootie Arlo’s first birthday! It’s always such a joy when our sweet couples turn parents & come back, giving us another opportunity to celebrate with them! How we cherish getting to meet the newest members of their family! We instantly fell in love with the most adorable birthday boy and knew from the start that we wanted to make this day as special as he is!
⠀
Arlo’s mama, Elizabeth shared with us his favorite picture book that she would read to him each night - Hello, hello!  It became the perfect inspiration to drive our design! This book explores seeing & appreciating nature & all of our endangered species. We were excited to create a space that would allow big and little guests to experience this book and enter it’s curios world!
⠀
Quotes from the book were woven throughout the event and a “Hello Neighbor, Hello Friend” wall with stuffed endangered species invited each of the kids to adopt one to take home at the end of the party. Another “Hello Land + Hello Sea” wall held different sensory bins filled with textures & toy animals and was a favorite place where the little ones could play throughout the party! Guests were welcomed to snack on yummy grilled cheese + ice cream sandwiches underneath striped fabric covered cabanas accented with whimsy balloons and florals while seated down to place settings that mimicked lion manes. A check-patterned bar that was nestled between trees served up cocktails that played to all of the different animals in the book inviting the adults to sip on a “Something Whoa,” and “Something Wild,” while the littles sipped on a mocktail named “Something Tame.”
⠀
And of course, nothing says first birthday like a smash cake! Sweet Arlo gave his cake a gentle massage before diving in! 😂 it was such an incredible day to be a part of and we’re so grateful for our team that came together for our favorite party animals!

It’s a good @martha_weddings morning! We’re so thrilled to see our elegant and effervescent Deia & Stephen and their cinematic-inspired whimsical wedding featured! There were so many details and moments and color, LOTS OF COLOR that made their event a highlight to our summer!
⠀
From design to creation we pulled together a team that helped us beautifully tell their story and one worthy of rivaling the most romantic of on-screen romances! It was the kind of day these two had always dreamed of…well one a little more than another 😉 Listen for the cute call out in their video trailer!
⠀
So beyond grateful for our dreamers & dream makers! Swing by @martha_weddings to see more!
⠀

I wanted to be a mother long before I knew I wanted to be anything else. I’m sure this was due in large part to the beautiful influences  of motherhood I had in my life. They were many. From women at church who taught me service, to aunts and grandmas and to my own mother most of all who supported me, listened to me, laughed with me and loved on me even when at times I fell short on loving myself while growing up. They were all there teaching me what it was to be a woman, a nurturer, a friend and a caregiver. They taught me patience and goodness and I wanted nothing more than to become like them. And so I waited. I waited longer than I initially ever had plans for to become a mama and felt the painful pull of wanting to be there sooner but i knew I was stepping into hallow ground when the day came and I held my first baby in my arms. It felt difficult, challenging and beautiful all at the same time and I loved it. I loved being a mother. Their mother. I am forever grateful for the gift that I have been given to be the one that holds their little hands through this life as they grow and as long as they’ll let me. They are my treasure and greatest joy. 
I continue to learn and be rallied around by amazing women every day. I see examples of motherhood and mothering everywhere and often as those mamas are preparing to celebrate their children on a wedding day and place that little hand they’ve held for so many years into the hand of someone else. It’s a rare and beautiful thing to witness the emotions that come with the milestones and I’m so grateful for all of it. Happy Mother’s Day to all of the incredible women that have made a difference in this world and changed it for the better. ❤️

“Something pretty always calls for a party” ✨

- Heather Balliet

It’s been quite a weekend for our A team over here as our very own beautiful Mackenzie Jean got married!! 🎉 Cue all the happy tears 😭 We couldn’t be more overjoyed that she found Ryan who we equally love and adore! He is the down-to-earth, jeans and t-shirt, tall & handsome kinda guy who wins your heart over quickly and just who she had been waiting for! As we’ve poured ourselves into weddings together we could only have dreamed of a love like this one day for her!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Skip and Tracy thank you for sharing your daughter with us all these years! You have raised one of my favorite people and it was an honor to celebrate with you! We know we should hold off and wait for the photos from @thesophiepton that are sure to be gorgeous but we simply can’t help ourselves in wanting to shout it from the rooftops so our phone photos will have to do for now! The wedding took place at our home/office @chezballiet (Mackenzie’s other second home) where we spend our hours planning 😉 which brought things full circle in the most magical of ways. From the office to the aisle and beyond we love you, Mack!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Thanks to our incredible team of friendors who made this day all that it was! @adorefolklore @poseypop @catalogatelier @heytherecupcake_ @backupbackdrops @danielleryanbeauty @secondsong_official @fourthingspaper @bbjlatavola @hostesshaven @vibycreative and @thesophiepton 🫶

Mirror mirror on the wall, which yummy mocktail will make you fall … in love?
⠀
To play to Morgyn and Hunter’s way of saying goodbye to each other and a cute way to end a couple’s quarrel we created a signature “Three Kisses” lavender lemonade and a kiwi strawberry spritzer that reads “Pinky Promises” for guests to sip on and enjoy!

The last time we were in Cabo we were with family & friends and Marcus was there. Ten short months later we lost him from this world. Being back here this week has come with so many feelings, memories & reminders of how much can change in just one year. He believed in pushing yourself towards growth & outside of what was comfortable. He was an avid reader and learner like Troy and had just discovered the benefits of a cold plunge. After a morning of exploring we sat in a pool of ice cold water to honor him and for 3 min we breathed through it, deep breaths, Troy quietly encouraging me, holding my hands, supporting me. I whispered “for Marcus”, tears running down my cheeks, sitting in the pain but knowing I was safe.  I stayed, committed, knowing we could endure it together. It was for but just a moment but felt like an allegory of our lifetime, a beautiful representation of the last 20 years… our anniversary. We would hold hands through the tears and the years, through Troy’s brain surgery as newlyweds,  the birth of four beautiful children, and through hundreds of weddings..literally hundreds of weddings! We would witness old and new love, experience the heartbreak and loss of family to suicide, a miscarriage, severed fingers from a table saw, and severed faith in what grew to be our mixed faith marriage and yet we would also feel the clarity, awakening and joy that would come from hard things, of learning a deeper definition of love that was unconditional, that allowed for the authenticity of honest and hard conversations, even when perspectives shifted and didn’t match the way you assumed they always would.  We would keep breathing through it together. We would show up and support each other, listen .. so much listening to get to a place of understanding. We kept holding hands, laughing together, crying together, raising babies together, failing & succeeding as parents together and dancing, always dancing in the kitchen together.  Happy anniversary my love.
